      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I've tested dozens of AI development platforms over the past two years. Some are clunky. Some are overpriced. Some lock you into one model provider and throw a fit when you want to switch.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Dify is none of those things.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "It's an open-source platform that lets you build production-ready AI applications — chatbots, autonomous agents, and retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) pipelines — without wrestling with low-level code. And after spending serious time with it, I can say it's one of the most thoughtfully designed tools in the AI space right now.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Let me walk you through what Dify is, what makes it special, and why it might be the missing piece in your AI stack.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l0",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://affiliate.dify.ai/ehm5uywvxx1s"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Start building with Dify today",
            "marks": [
              "l0"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What Exactly Is Dify?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Dify (short for \"Do it for you\") is an open-source platform for building applications powered by large language models. Think of it as a visual IDE specifically designed for LLM-based workflows.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Instead of writing hundreds of lines of Python to wire up an LLM call, connect it to a vector database, add a prompt template, and deploy it as an API, Dify gives you a drag-and-drop canvas where you do all of that visually. You can:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Build chatbots",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " that pull answers from your own documents",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Create AI agents",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " that use tools, make decisions, and take actions",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Design RAG pipelines",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " that retrieve context from uploaded knowledge bases",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Orchestrate multi-step workflows",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " where different models and tools interact",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The platform supports all major LLM providers — OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Mistral, local models via Ollama, and many more through Hugging Face. You're never locked into a single vendor.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "And because it's open-source, you can self-host the entire thing on your own infrastructure. Full control, full privacy, full flexibility.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How Dify Works Under the Hood",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Here's what makes Dify click. The platform is built around a few core concepts:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "1. Apps",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " — These are your end products. A chatbot is an app. A document Q&A system is an app. A multi-agent workflow is an app. You pick the app type that fits your use case.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "2. Prompts",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " — Dify has a built-in prompt IDE where you write, test, and iterate on prompts with real-time previews. You can use variables, chain prompts together, and even A/B test different versions.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "3. Knowledge Bases",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " — Upload documents (PDFs, Notion pages, websites, CSVs) and Dify automatically chunks, embeds, and indexes them into a vector store. When your app receives a question, it searches the knowledge base for relevant context before generating an answer.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "4. Tools & Plugins",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " — Give your AI agent access to web search, calculators, image generators, or custom API calls. Dify handles the tool-calling logic so your agent can reason about which tool to use and when.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "5. Workflows",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " — This is where things get powerful. Dify's visual workflow editor lets you chain LLM calls, conditional logic, code nodes, and tool executions into complex pipelines. It's like building a flowchart, except each node actually does something.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The beauty is in the abstraction. You're not sacrificing power for simplicity. You're gaining speed without losing control.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l1",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/how-to-use-dify"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you want a detailed walkthrough, check our ",
            "marks": []
