    "image_prompt": "Editorial tech thumbnail, 16:9. Incorporate the brand logo fetched from https://logo.clearbit.com/dify.ai as the clean focal element over a soft amber-to-cream gradient (Notion + Apple aesthetic). A developer sitting at a clean desk with multiple screens showing flowcharts and AI workflow nodes, soft blue and purple lighting, minimalist office space. Glassmorphism cards, soft volumetric light, generous negative space for a title, no embedded text, no watermark. --ar 16:9 --style raw",
    "faq_items": [
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Is Dify really free to use?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Yes. Dify offers a free tier that includes app creation, knowledge base uploads, and API access with reasonable rate limits. It's open-source, so you can also self-host the entire platform at no cost. Paid plans add team collaboration, higher limits, and priority support.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Do I need coding skills to use Dify?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "No advanced coding is required. The visual workflow builder, drag-and-drop interface, and built-in prompt editor let you create sophisticated AI applications without writing backend code. Basic understanding of how LLMs work helps, but Dify handles the infrastructure.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Can I use Dify with my own data and keep it private?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Absolutely. Dify supports self-hosting on your own servers, which means your data stays within your infrastructure. You can connect it to any LLM provider, including locally-hosted models through Ollama or private API endpoints, for complete data control.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      }
